SIMPLE: incorporation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incorporation
<hw>In*cor`po*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>incorporatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>incorporation</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of incorporating, or the state of being
incorporated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The union of different ingredients in one mass;
mixture; combination; synthesis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The union of something with a body already existing;
association; intimate union; assimilation; <as>as, the
<ex>incorporation</ex> of conquered countries into the Roman
republic</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The act of creating a
corporation.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A body incorporated; a
corporation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incorporative</ent>⟦br⟧
